    <worksheet name='Profit Margin Distribution by Region (Order-Level)'>
      <layout-options>
        <caption>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>“The box plot reveals that Central is not just underperforming — it is structurally unstable. It has the lowest median profit margin, the highest variability, and the most extreme negative outliers. This indicates inconsistent pricing or discounting strategies leading to frequent and sometimes severe losses. In contrast, West shows stable and consistently positive margins, indicating better control over pricing and discount practices.”</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </caption>
      </layout-options>
      <table>
        <view>
          <datasources>
            <datasource caption='Sheet1 (SuperStore Sales DataSet)' name='federated.0851brr08q3wbf1h5glde00p5wbj' />
          </datasources>
